### Context

This is a dataset from Yuen Peng Loh and Chee Seng Chan. Here is the paper (https://arxiv.org/abs/1805.11227). It is a dataset for object detection in the dark environment and image enhancement. **IT IS NOT CREATED BY ME!!**

There is github link: https://github.com/cs-chan/Exclusively-Dark-Image-Dataset


### Content

The images are kept in individual class folders following the image class labels:

1. Bicycle - 652 images
2. Boat - 679 images
3. Bottle - 547 images
4. Bus - 527 images
5. Car - 638 images
6. Cat - 735 images
7. Chair - 648 images
8. Cup - 519 images
9. Dog - 801 images
10. Motorbike - 503 images
11. People - 609 images
12. Table - 505 images

Total : 7,363 images

(a) Training - 3,000 images (250 images per class)

(b) Validation - 1,800 images (150 images per class)

(c) Testing - 2,563 images


### Acknowledgements

From Yuen Peng Loh and Chee Seng Chan's paper "Getting to know low-light images with the Exclusively Dark dataset (https://arxiv.org/abs/1805.11227).
